 SF in 3/4 of the sources. We compare our LSF and LAGN to lower\nredshift samples and show a new correlation between LSF and mbh. We also\nexamine several rather speculative ideas about the host galaxy properties\nincluding the possibility that the detected sources are above the SF mass\nsequence (MS) at z=4.8, perhaps in mergers, and most of the undetected sources\nare on the MS.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 31 Jul 2013 20:00:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 7 Aug 2013 09:34:54 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 3 Jun 2014 09:56:44 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-16"}
