cope aperture and\nrotated by a superconducting magnetic bearing. The observation program consists\nof at least two, five-day flights beginning with the 150 GHz observations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 1 Aug 2013 15:07:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 9 Dec 2013 16:27:21 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sun, 5 Jan 2014 19:17:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-07-29"}
